\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs48\cf1\up0\dn0 Loading/Saving Games}{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\b\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 Loading a Game:}{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 From the opening screen, select "Load Game" from the menu, or hit the F1 key.  }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 This will bring up a game selection screen which allows you to load any valid }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 4000 A.D. game file.  Games are saved in a compressed format ending in ".zlb".}{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 You can save/load game files anywhere in your computer, although it is a good }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 idea to keep them in one place, preferably in the same directory as the game }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 itself (or in a subdirectory).}{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 Click on a game filename, then click the "Start Game" button (or double-click the }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 filename) to begin.  If you are Player 2 and it is your first turn, you will be }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 prompted to supply a name for yourself and for your home planet. If you do not }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 supply a name for your planet, a random name will be assigned.}{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\b\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 Saving a Game:}{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 Click on the Save Game button at the lower left corner of the main game screen. }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 This will bring up the Save Game screen, where you may select one of 5 games  }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 to save the turn in.  The game number to be saved is selected by default to }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 prevent accidentally overwriting another game, although you can select another }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 game to save into.  }{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 The saved game file is automatically named to allow for easy identification when }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 {\ul sending the turn by email}{\v sending_the_turn_by_email } to your opponent (with your choice of internet mail }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 program):}{
\par}\pard
