K{\footnote BioChemical Warfare}
+{\footnote final:0080}

\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs48\cf1\up0\dn0 BioChemical Warfare}{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 The damage done to a planet's resource production capacity by a biochemical }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 rocket attack goes beyond anything that can be repaired, the way industry can }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 be repaired after a sabotage attack.  The planet must first be detoxified, and only }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 then can its capacity to produce resources be regenerated.  Both of these steps }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 require technologies that must be researched.  Without detoxification the planet }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 cannot support human life, and each turn some of your human troops stationed }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 on the planet will die slow, agonizing deaths.  Mechanized Assault troops }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 (Mechs), however, are not affected by the toxic environment.}{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\b\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\b\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 Launching Biohazard Rockets:}{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 Once you have researched this technology, you can launch these horrific and }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 destructive chemical weapons at your opponents' planets.  Further research will }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 extend the range of these rockets.  Each rocket launch costs 30 Resources.}{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 After launching you will be informed of the rocket's ETA, and again when the }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 rocket hits its target.  The rockets are not foolproof, however, and the chances of }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 the rocket being destroyed before impact will vary depending on the target }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 planet's defenses.}{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 The initial explosion of a rocket has a devastating effect on human troops, with a }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 reduced impact on mechs, and resource production is usually wiped out }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 completely.  Until the planet's environment is cleaned up (requiring Detoxification }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 research), casualties among human troops will continue to be high, whereas }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 mechs are not affected after the initial impact.  Once a planet's environment has }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 been detoxified, its resource production capacity can be regenerated (requiring }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 Resource Regeneration research).}{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql{\f0\fs18\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql{\f0\fs18\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql{\f0\fs18\cf0\up0\dn0 Helpfile generated by VB HelpWriter.}{
\par}\pard
