#{\footnote Hlp_Combat_Overview}
${\footnote Combat Overview}
K{\footnote Combat Overview}
+{\footnote final:0070}

\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs48\cf1\up0\dn0 Combat Overview}{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 When you land on a neutral planet, your forces claim it for your empire without }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 any trouble from the locals.  When you land on a planet held by your opponent or }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 by the {\ul Melnikons}{\v Melnikons }, however, your ship goes into Attack mode. }{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 Victory is determined by a comparison of each side's {\ul Combat Strength}{\v Combat_Strength }, with ties }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 going to the defender.}{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 The results of the combat are displayed in the {\ul Landscape View}{\v Landscape_View } window. If you }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 win, the planet is yours.  If you lose, your attacking force is wiped out, but not }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 before they send back a report on the planet indicating the level of defenses, }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 technology and resource production.  }{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 *Note: if you successfully invade a planet with advanced technologies such as }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 missile bases, planetary shields or scanners, those items are destroyed in the }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 battle.  Advanced resource production facilities remain are not  destroyed, }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 however, and the increased production continues as the spoils of victory. }{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\b\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 The Alien Menace}{
\par}\pard
\ql\li0\fi0\ri-28096{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 There is also a chance that your weaker planets will be subjected to an alien }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 invasion. The cowardly Melnikons prey on poorly-defended planets only, so it is }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 advised that planets have at least 4 troops or 1 mech to defend against this }
\ql{\f0\fs24\cf0\up0\dn0 threat.  }{
\par}\pard
\ql{\f0\fs18\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
\ql{\f0\fs18\cf0\up0\dn0
\par}\pard
